## Output Schema
Return a JSON array of mate constraints. Each object has exactly these fields:

[
  {
    "part_a": "component_name_1",
    "part_b": "component_name_2",
    "constraint_type": "planar",
    "description": "bottom face of cover sits flat on top face of base_plate"
  }
]

Constraint types:
- "planar"      — two flat faces are coincident (flush or offset)
- "cylindrical" — a pin/shaft mates into a hole or bore
- "fixed"       — parts are rigidly bonded (welded, press-fit, or glued)
- "sliding"     — parts can translate along one axis (rail/slot)

Rules:
- Only include constraints between components that physically touch or mate.
- If only one component exists, return an empty array [].
- Use exact component names from the list above.
